Guns are legal in the U.S. and not the U.K.<br>
Therefore...<br>
Legalized guns are the cause of the greater number of murders in the U.S.<br>
<br>
Correlation does not equal causality.<br>
<br>
I would be very interested in a study which can prove whether this one factor, legalized presence of a particular weapon (firearms), makes a significant difference in how much people kill each other.<br>
<br>
Liberal rhetoric notwithstanding, until some such study comes out, I will continue to believe that factors such as personal irresponsibility, social and cultural pressures, etc. have a much greater deal to do with murder rates in particular places than whether or not someone has access to a particular (easily replaceable) tool.<br>
<br>
