<br>
You may be correct, Shehbahn.  I don't know, I haven't looked up the numbers.<br>
<br>
But even if you are, there are so many other factors involved that it still would not convince me that, by giving up the right to legally own a gun, there would be a significant enough increase in freedom from crime to warrant it.<br>
<br>
Guns are a tool, nothing more.  Having an easily accessible tool might make an action easier, and the unavailability of a tool might make an action more difficult to the point where the perpetrator decides it's not worth the trouble.  But in either of these cases, the basic problem remains - the fact that the perpetrator, whether he performs the action or not, wants to kill someone else.  Removing a tool is a half-solution at best, that addresses none of the true underlying problems.  It is not worth it, to me, to remove the right to bear arms from law abiding, intelligent, responsible citizens in order to possibly prevent such a tool from falling into the hands of criminal, stupid, irresponsible people.  Better to deal with the people that commit crimes rather than what they commit them with.  Especially when that tool can be used to not only commit, but prevent crime.  The degree to which you agree with that last statement may vary, but nobody can rationally deny it completely. <p>Caledhon TelRana - 53 Warrior<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701">
Vethantis Soulbonker</a> - 57 Enchanter<br><b>Revolution</b>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucaledhontelrana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caledhon TelRana</A> at: 8/7/02 11:27:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uwenin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wenin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/7/02 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aradcliff.net/images/130.gif width=128 height=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gun Control and Crime, the English experience</span><hr size=1> Kell is right on the money.<br>
<br>
You can't seriously compare how a law or government policy will affect the populations of two seperate countries.  There are so many different factors that come to play, when you're looking at the impact that such things would have on a society.<br>
<br>
The comparing of such things is just plain ignorance.  Such people are essentially believing that people are people.  A person from England, thinks just like some person from France.  If the events in the last year, havn't woken us up to the fact that people can be very different, we'll forever be left ignorant.<br>
<br>
Think of it this way.  If we took all the criminals from the US prisons, inserted them into a prison in the UK, to carry out the rest of their term.  Do you believe that when they're released into the enlightened United Kingdom, that they'd fly the straight and narrow?<br>
<br>
We're dealing with a different situation in the States, than those in the UK, or any other country.  If we want to have a better understanding of how a law will affect our populace, we'll be looking to compare our different states to each other, rather than looking for comparisions from the outside.<br>
<br>
I certainly don't see any Garden of Eden out there, that's for sure. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094">Wenin Huirunda</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg>TheTribunal.org</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36>Reality Sinks In</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org/">Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <!-- .. -->
